{"title":"New POC Elicit Ti glasses cost £350 and use recycled titanium to save one whole gram","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-elicit-ti-sunglasses","date":1683810000000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-elicit-ti-sunglasses\">New POC Elicit Ti glasses cost £350 and use recycled titanium to save one whole gram</a></p>\n\n<p>POC has used recycled medical grade titanium in its new, limited edition Elicit Ti <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/clothing/sunglasses\">cycling sunglasses</a>, which it says reduces the weight to 22g, making the new sunnies its lightest ever. Paired with its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/poc-ventral-lite-helmet-review\">Ventral Lite helmet</a>, POC says the combination can weigh as little as 200 grams. The Elicit Ti glasses are priced at £350, $400, €400 or AU$575.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Elicit is a frameless sunglass design, but while the standard <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-elicit-clarity-sunglasses\">Elicit</a> glasses have Grilamid plastic sidearms, in the Elicit Ti these are substituted by a trussed titanium design, which POC reckons shaves one gram (yes, one!) off the glasses’ weight, as well as making them stronger.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"646\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-970x646.jpg\" alt=\"POC Elicit Ti sunglasses sidearms\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-768x511.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-1536x1023.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-750x499.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-1140x759.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/POC_Elicit-Ti_2023-video_041.jpg 2002w\" /><figcaption>POC</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>POC’s titanium comes from waste generated in making surgical tools, which is salvaged, refined and reformed in Sweden. The manufacturing process uses a laser to 3D print the sidearms, with the unused titanium powder recycled for use in subsequent batches.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-propel-sunglasses\">Yes, even your sunglasses can be aero: Meet the POC Propel</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-elicit-clarity-sunglasses\">Poc launches Elicit Clarity, its lightest ever glasses weighing just 23g</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-cycling-sunglasses\">Best cycling sunglasses: look good on the bike</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>According to Tilda Håll, Product Manager, Eyewear at POC: ‘We approached the development of the Elicit Ti with a basic principle at its core; that sustainable materials and performance can, and should, be able to live side by side.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Elicit Ti’s design allows quick lens changes using slide-in joints and also allows the sidearms to break away in a crash to help prevent injury.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"650\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-970x650.jpeg\" alt=\"POC Elicit Ti sunglasses\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-970x650.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-300x201.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-768x515.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-1536x1030.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-2048x1373.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-750x503.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/05/EL100_ElicitTi_1027_Titanium_Violet_SilverMirror_00011-1140x764.jpeg 1140w\" /><figcaption>POC</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Other features of the Elicit Ti include POC’s single-piece, curved Clarity lens, which is treated with POC’s Ri-Pel coating to protect the lens from dirt, water, sweat and other contaminants and is anti-scratch treated. The glasses are supplied with two sizes of nosepiece, a spare clear lens and a hard case. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Elicit Ti sunglasses are currently seeing action at the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia</a> with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/ef-education-easypost\" target=\"_blank\">EF Education-EasyPost</a> team.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The standard Elicit glasses don’t come cheap at £220, but adding the titanium sidearms increases that to £350, $400, €400 or AU$575. Full details at <a href=\"http://www.pocsports.com/products/elicit-ti\" target=\"_blank\">POC</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Check out our guide to the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/buyers-guide-cycling-sunglasses\" target=\"_blank\">best cycling sunglasses</a>.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/poc-elicit-ti-sunglasses\">New POC Elicit Ti glasses cost £350 and use recycled titanium to save one whole gram</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"pnorman","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"4c371ce99076b4c7412e15df5c30c36818016bb729e55dc41c7b38f2263db9e5","category":"Cycling"}